\title{Power notation}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-13}
\taxon{definition}
\MML{group_1}{def 8}{K5}

\p{Let #{G} be a [[gr-000G]], let #{g\in G}, let #{n\in\NN_{0}} be a non-negative integer. We write #{g^{n}} and define it inductively by
##{g^{0}=e}
and
##{g^{n+1}=g\star g^{n}.}
We can extend this to integer exponents by defining
##{g^{-n}=(g^{-1})^{n}.}}